# NestJS API (`apps/api`)

## Module layout

```
apps/api/src/
  auth/          # MSAL OIDC flow, passport-jwt session strategy, RolesGuard
  tasks/         # CRUD, status changes, comments, reassignment
  events/        # task_events persistence + BullMQ enqueue
  workers/       # task-events processor + health cron (@nestjs/bullmq)
  intel/         # SSE feed, leaderboard, momentum, RAG query
  common/        # guards, decorators, filters
```

## Auth â€” MSAL Node (OIDC) + passport-jwt (session)

`passport-azure-ad` is **deprecated**. Backend owns auth:

1. `GET /auth/login` â†’ MSAL `getAuthCodeUrl()` â†’ redirect to Entra
2. `GET /auth/callback` â†’ MSAL `acquireTokenByCode()` â†’ read `oid`/`name`/`email`/`groups` claims â†’ upsert user â†’ sign **app session JWT** (`@nestjs/jwt`, `JWT_SECRET`) with `{ sub, role }`
3. Frontends send session JWT as `Authorization: Bearer` â†’ `passport-jwt` strategy validates it

```typescript
// jwt.strategy.ts â€” validates the app's own session token
@Injectable()
export class JwtStrategy extends PassportStrategy(Strategy) {
  constructor() {
    super({
      jwtFromRequest: ExtractJwt.fromAuthHeaderAsBearerToken(),
      ignoreExpiration: false,
      secretOrKey: process.env.JWT_SECRET,
    });
  }
  async validate(payload: { sub: string; role: Role }) {
    return { userId: payload.sub, role: payload.role };
  }
}
```

Map Entra group object IDs (env) â†’ role at callback time. `pulse-viewer` has no Board write access.

## RBAC guard pattern

```typescript
// roles.decorator.ts
export const ROLES_KEY = 'roles';
export const Roles = (...roles: Role[]) => SetMetadata(ROLES_KEY, roles);

// usage
@Roles('pulse-admin', 'pulse-member')
@UseGuards(AuthGuard('jwt'), RolesGuard)
@Post('/tasks')
createTask(...) {}
```

`RolesGuard` reads `ROLES_KEY` via `Reflector.getAllAndOverride` and checks `user.role`.

## Event emission

Every mutation: INSERT `task_events` â†’ UPDATE `tasks.last_activity_at` â†’ enqueue `task-events` job with canonical `TaskEvent` DTO from `@pulse/shared-types`. Workers JOIN `tasks` + `users` to enrich context â€” keep the payload minimal.

## Workers (`@nestjs/bullmq`)

`BullModule.forRoot({ connection })` + `registerQueue({ name: QUEUES.TASK_EVENTS })`. One `@Processor` extends `WorkerHost` (separate processors on the same queue would compete for jobs):

```typescript
@Processor(QUEUES.TASK_EVENTS)
export class TaskEventsProcessor extends WorkerHost {
  async process(job: Job<TaskEvent>) {
    // enrich â†’ embed â†’ recomputeForTask(taskId) â†’ realtime.broadcast
  }
}
```

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| Embed | content_text â†’ DashScope embed â†’ `event_embeddings` |
| Health | `HealthService.recomputeForTask(taskId)` after each event |
| Realtime | push event into the SSE stream (below) |
| Cron | `HealthService.recomputeAll()` every 15 min â€” safety net |

## SSE realtime (Intel feed)

Native NestJS `@Sse()` returning an RxJS `Observable`. A shared `Subject<TaskEvent>` bridges the realtime processor and the stream:

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class RealtimeService {
  readonly stream$ = new Subject<TaskEvent>();   // processor calls .next(event)
}

@Controller('intel')
export class IntelSseController {
  constructor(private realtime: RealtimeService) {}

  @Sse('feed')
  feed(): Observable<MessageEvent> {
    return this.realtime.stream$.pipe(map((event) => ({ data: event })));
  }
}
```

No reconnect/persistence logic â€” POC scope.

## RAG endpoint

`POST /intel/query`: load chat history â†’ live health snapshot (leaderboard top 15) â†’ embed question â†’ pgvector top-10 with `tasks.health_score` joined â†’ enrich source text via `health-context.ts` â†’ Qwen stream with history + health snapshot + events â†’ persist `intel_chat_turns`.

